United announced on Monday evening that the 63-year-old mentor was advised by the club s medical department to seek specialist advice after battling with some health issues over the last few days. The Briton will miss Tuesday night s league encounter against Bidvest Wits at Bidvest Stadium and the premiership match against his former club Kaizer Chiefs in Nelspruit on Saturday night.Baxter apparently suffered great discomfort in his side s Nedbank Cup quarter final win against Chiefs at FNB Stadium on Saturday night and struggled throughout the game.United announced that his assistant Kaitano Tembo will take over the coaching reins in his absence. -TMG Digital/TMG Sport